      "We could also/instead use the `title` attribute on the 'run', 'clear', ... to show the keyboard shortcut. That's how jsfiddle does it. \r\n\r\n![screen shot 2015-02-17 at 10 45 02 am](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1981198/6234781/5e4731a4-b692-11e4-8517-811a6d93d221.png)\r\n![screen shot 2015-02-17 at 10 45 08 am](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1981198/6234782/5e480a2a-b692-11e4-94e9-ffe05e3f6d80.png)\r\n\r\nThe mark is obviously pretty simple: \r\n\r\n```\r\n<a class=\"aiButton\" id=\"run\" title=\"Run (CTRL + Return)\" href=\"#run\"><span class=\"icon-caret-right\"></span>Run</a>\r\n```\r\n\r\n(I had to find this thread to know that there were keyboard shortcuts!)"
